Vasco Chaya LIFESTYLE WRITER chayav@dailynews.co.zw ZIMBABWEANS have launched a campaign to mobilise votes for outstanding musician Sha sha after she was nominated in the celebrated BET awards, a fete which saw her becoming the first local to receive such a prestigious honour. The Amapiano Queen was nominated in the Viewers’ Choice: Best New International Act alongside Nigeria’s Rema Celeste, Young T and Bugsey (UK), Hatik and Stacy (France). Born in Mutare, Sha sha whose real name is Charmaine Mapimbiro, hogged international limelight after featuring Samthing Soweto on the hit Akulaleki.   VOTING LINK: https://www.bet.com/shows/bet-awards/2020/nominees/viewers-choice-best-new-international-act.html